                <div class="comment-content">
                    <p>Roger, I buy these organic broccoli florets that come in packs. I take a handful out, wash them a bit, and just throw them on top of my rice while it's on WARM inside the rice cooker (the veggie cooks in about twenty minutes, coming out still green and fresh-looking). Very convenient, no need to steam them separately. I also reheat my overnight viands this way, to take to work as packed lunch, or what we call "bien-dang".</p>
