                    <p>I'm more of a Crock Pot person, but I bet that your Pot is better at cooking grains than any Crock Pot is. The lid on a Crock Pot is not as tight as the lid on a rice cooker, so it loses a lot of moisture in cooking. No good for rice, oatmeal, or wheat berries.</p>

<p>I might be sold on a rice cooker now.</p>
