                    <p>The potato poem is another gem which points to the beauties of the life less encumbered---I always love Van Gogh's painting of  his "Room",in fact I have a small print of it hanging in my own place--just a bed and a table and a towel hanging from the peg.I visited once Mahatma Gandhi's place of detention in the Agha Khan palace in Pune in Western India---his posessions amounted to his wooden footwear,spectacles,his favourite Bhagwatgita and another item or two..Even films are valuable insofar they enable us to explore and polish the grandeur of the inner universe which is the common heritage of a human being.The pot which you have so eloquently and poetically  described also has a certain austere technological and utilitarian beauty with its relative simplicity like the pots of olden times.Long live pots !</p>
