                <div class="comment-content">
                    <p>Any idiot can make good rice using a simple rice cooker, but it takes a special kind of idiot, such as me, to screw it up.  In an attempt to make the meal even healthier, I used filtered water with the rice.  Unfortunately the water came from my Brita pitcher straight from the refrigerator, and apparently near frozen water has a way of tricking the cooker into thinking it is prematurely done.  I still use filtered water with my rice, but now I let it warm to room temperature before cooking.</p>
