                <div class="comment-content">
                    <p>I think ...<br />
British Usage: periods and commas outside the closing quotes.<br />
American Usage: periods and commas inside the closing quotes.<br />
I am happy to be corrected, but that's my understanding.<br />
I, by the way, am guided generally by the Chicago Manual of Style.</p>

<p><b> Ebert: The University of Chicago Press has [U.S.]  have [U.K.]  published two of my books, in which you will observe that I follow the Chicago Manual of Style in even the smallest details, without exception. </b></p>
