                <div class="comment-content">
                    <p>Miss Inas Down Home Rice Pudding</p>

<p><br />
2 cups of rice<br />
Three cups of water<br />
 stick of butter<br />
Tsp. of cinnamon<br />
Tsp. of vanilla extract<br />
 tsp. of nutmeg<br />
 cup of pet milk<br />
 cups of brown or white sugar </p>

<p>Combine all these ingredients in the rice cooker.  The cooker will turn off when done.</p>

<p>Heat oven to 350 degrees</p>

<p>Pour the cooked rice into greased baking casserole dish; cook in the oven for about thirty minutes or forty minutes.</p>

<p>The pudding will serve about four to six people. </p>

<p><b> Uncle Roger: Or three other people and me. </b><br />
</p>
