                <div class="comment-content">
                    <p>Hey, can't wait for the book to come out, as I love my rice cooker, but have never gotten around to trying anything "adventurous" on it yet. Not sure if this is at all helpful, but it's my basic rice recipe that satisfies my craving for something slightly salty, but which is better for you than, say, pizza or a cheeseburger. </p>

<p>1. Make white rice, but use less water than normal and instead add some soy sauce, and a squirt of that spicy red chili sauce in the bottle with the green lid and the Chinese characters on it. [Optionally, you could just make the rice normally, and add the sauces later]<br />
2. At some point while it's cooking, add a drained can of tuna (or don't drain it, whatever). <br />
3. When it's done, sprinkle sesame seeds on top. <br />
4. Eat it. I usually have a salad with no dressing and piece of fruit on the side. Enjoy! </p>
                </div>
