                    <p>Glad to see someone who actually uses the rice cooker for other things aside from just rice.  I've never really gotten around to experimenting with it yet, aside from trying my hand at making congee.  As a college student, however, being able to toss a frozen fish and adding an egg and soy sauce have proven to be quite handy with rice, among other delicious alternatives.  </p>

<p>Zojirushi's fancy rice cookers are actually quite spectacular.  My mom has only just upgraded our rice cooker from the previous one (ten years strong from almost DAILY use).  I've seen wondrous things concocted.  I have to ask my mom, but one of the things she makes quite well is steamed fried rice.  I have to ask her for the exact recipe, but it involves chopped duck and liver sausage, shiitake mushrooms, bok choi, and some type of sauce.  To be continued...</p>

