                    <p>Dear Roger, </p>

<p>I read this post on rice cookers a year ago but consulted it again just now because Amazon notified me of a small appliance sale and I had committed prior to my recent birthday to finally geting a Zojirushi rice cooker. I was at a Korean friend's home recently where of course a rice cooker was set up for guests to serve themselves. When I asked her if she preferred that brand, she replied in the affirmative but still gave me a funny look like she didn't really get the point of the question. I think it may have been like asking "Do your kitchen faucets work well?" A rice cooker cooks rice. Like the children's book says "Everybody cooks rice."</p>

