                <div class="comment-content">
                    <p>Really nice post, here is my recipe. </p>

<p>Velout de lgumes</p>

<p>One head of broccoli (If you dont love broccoli then you dont put broccoli).<br />
2 carrots<br />
2 potatoes<br />
1 onion<br />
2 branches of celery<br />
1 liter of chicken broth (could also be vegetable broth)<br />
 Cup of milk (could be fresh cream)</p>

<p>Cut everything in small cube and put it in the pot. Wait for the carrot to be well cooked and stop the pot (carrot is the longest thing to cook).</p>

<p>Let it rest for 5 min approx, add the milk and mix everything with a hand blender (which is an essential for me in the kitchen). </p>

<p>Then all you have to do is adjust the seasoning. Salt. Pepper. Fresh herbs could be good. Some parmesan on top will do the job (parmesan always do the job). A tea spoon of curry could also be a good idea. One splash of olive oil and youre ready to go.</p>

<p>This is a winner every time. Tasty. Full of vitamins. Could be served as an entre or a main dish with croutons and cheese.<br />
</p>
                </div>
            </div>
