                </div>
                <div class="comment-content">
                    <p>Great article, Roger; I'm definitely going to be getting a copy of the new book!</p>

<p>I'm adding a recipe I came up with recently.</p>

<p>Make some Texmati rice (I usually throw in a tad of butter and some salt a la the directions on the side of the package).</p>

<p>While the rice is cooking, cut up around 4-6 stalks of green onions and pan-fry with a little Pam until they're just this side of brown.  </p>

<p>Do the same thing with 4-6 cloves of garlic sliced as thin as you're able.  (The concept of 'too much garlic' doesn't exist for me, and you might want to go a little tamer.)</p>

<p>Finally, take a stalk of cilantro and start chopping it up from the leaf end until you start getting more stems than leaves; a good handful of this is all you need.</p>

<p>Once the rice is done, stir in the cilantro, onions and garlic... and, voila :-)</p>

<p><br />
</p>
                </div>
            </div>
