                <div class="comment-content">
                    <p>I'm Cuban and we have had rice cookers since way back when.  The favorite, or most readily available in Florida is the Hitachi chime-o-matic. </p>

<p>We eat rice practically every day and it makes PERFECT rice every time.  I have never tried making anything else in it though.  </p>

<p>One of our family favorites?  Arroz con Salchichas.  Yellow rice with Vienna Sausage.  Saute your onions, green peppers, garlic in a little olive oil, add it to your rice, put in a packet of the McCormick "Sazon Seasoning" the one with Culantro and Anichote (corriander and Annatto) and throw in a few cans of Vienna Sausage (must be the pork, chicken and beef variety).  Sometimes my mom would also throw in a can of corn kernals.  I'm telling you, this is true Cuban comfort food.  And of course very economical, fast and quick to make (ready in 20 minutes) and simply delicious.</p>

<p>Try it, you'll like it.  I can't wait to get your book and see what else I can do on my Hitachi.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
