                <div class="comment-content">
                    <p>Because of my deep and abiding love for you Roger, I am going to share my recipe for Crock Pot Curried Potatoes. I guess you could use a rice pot to make this if you are stubborn.</p>

<p>Ingredients: </p>

<p>------------</p>

<p>01. 1 large potato, sweet potato, or yam.</p>

<p>02. Spice Hunter no-salt curry powder to taste.</p>

<p>03. Extra virgin olive oil.</p>

<p>04. 1 teaspoon Trader Joe's no salt hot sauce. </p>

<p>05. No salt garlic powder to taste.</p>

<p>06. 1 teaspoon Xylitol sugar or other healthy sugar substitute. </p>

<p>Instructions: </p>

<p>-------------</p>

<p>01. Dice the potato. Place in crock pot/rice cooker to cook thoroughly.</p>

<p>02. When the potatoes are soft, douse liberally with olive oil, then add all of the dry ingredients and mix thoroughly. So good. </p>

<p>Of course, the real point of having a humongous crock pot is that you can make a vast quantity of any recipe and then parcel it up in the freezer for healthy, low-salt homemade frozen dinners. </p>
                </div>
